                                    My own kids need help. How do I request clothes for them? <i class="fa fa-angle-down rotate-icon"></i>
                                </h5>
                            </a>
                        </div>
                        <!--/Card Header-->
                        <!--Card content-->
                        <div id="collapseFour" class="collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingFour">
                            <div class="card-block">
                                We do <strong>NOT</strong> accept clothing requests directly from parents in order to ensure the anonimity of the kids that we help.
                                If you need to request clothes for your own kids, please contact your child's school guidance counselor.
                                They can submit the request to us for your child and we will deliver the bag of clothing back to them to give to your child.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!--/Card content-->
                    </div>
                    <!--/Card-->
                    <!--Card-->
                    <div class="card">
                        <!--Card Header-->
                        <div class="card-header" role="tab" id="headingFive">
                            <a data-toggle="collapse" class="collapsed" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFive" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFive">
                                <h5 class="mb-0">
                                    Does my child have to be on welface, subsidized lunches, or other forms of financial assistance to get clothes? <i class="fa fa-angle-down rotate-icon"></i>
                                </h5>
                            </a>
                        </div>
                        <!--/Card Header-->
                        <!--Card content-->
                        <div id="collapseFive" class="collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingFive">
                            <div class="card-block">
                                No, we want to help all children that are truly in need of clothes.
                                We know that people who receive no outside financial assistance can go through hard times or disasters in life that can cause them to have immediate needs.
                                We want to help in these situations to ensure that your kids have the clothing they need.
                                However, we do our best to prioritize giving to children based on the level of need expressed to us by the requesting school.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!--/Card content-->
                    </div>
                    <!--/Card-->
                    <!--Card-->
                    <div class="card">
                        <!--Card Header-->
                        <div class="card-header" role="tab" id="headingSix">
                            <a data-toggle="collapse" class="collapsed" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseSix" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseSix">
                                <h5 class="mb-0">
                                    How long does it take to get clothes for my child? <i class="fa fa-angle-down rotate-icon"></i>
                                </h5>
                            </a>
                        </div>
                        <!--/Card Header-->
                        <!--Card content-->
                        <div id="collapseSix" class="collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingSix">
                            <div class="card-block">
                                As a parent you should work with your child's school guidance counselor to request clothes from us.
                                Once we receive the request from the school our normal delivery time is one week. However if the school indicates that the need is immediate, we will get the clothes to the school as soon as possible, usually within 48 hours.
                                If we do not have the correct sizes in stock for your child, we will notify the requestor so that they can let you know that there might be a delay before your child can receive clothes.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!--/Card content-->
